easyauth.customIdps.markdownDescription:
Custom OIDC providers (e.g. Auth0, Salesforce). Each entry is added to `IDP_LIST` and mapped to `IDP_<NAME>_*` environment variables, where `<NAME>` is the uppercased `name` field.

**Required fields per entry:** `name`, `clientId`, `oidcIssuerUrl`

Client secrets must be registered separately via the **EasyAuth Emulator: Set Client Secret** command (stored encrypted in the OS keychain).

**Example:**
```jsonc
{
  "easyauth.customIdps": [
    {
      "name": "my-provider",
      "displayName": "My Provider",
      "clientId": "your-client-id",
      "oidcIssuerUrl": "https://your-provider.example.com"
    }
  ]
}
```
